mitelIpGrpFilterGroup.name: mitelIpGrpFilterGroup
mitelIpGrpFilterGroup.contactinfo: Standards Group, Postal: MITEL Corporation 350 Legget Drive, PO Box 13089 Kanata, Ontario Canada K2K 1X3 Tel: +1 613 592 2122 Fax: +1 613 592 4784 E-mail: std@mitel.com

mitelFltGrpAccessRestrictEnable.name: mitelFltGrpAccessRestrictEnable
mitelFltGrpAccessRestrictEnable.description: This object indicates if the IP Access Restriction table is being used to filter or forward packets.

mitelFltGrpLogicalTable.name: mitelFltGrpLogicalTable
mitelFltGrpLogicalTable.description: A table containing information about logical IP LAN destinations.

mitelFltGrpLogicalEntry.name: mitelFltGrpLogicalEntry
mitelFltGrpLogicalEntry.description: Each entry of this table contains information about a specific logical interface toa local area network. Each logical LAN can support routing or bridging functions, these are considered virtual interfaces.

mitelLogTableAccessDef.name: mitelLogTableAccessDef
mitelLogTableAccessDef.description: This object indicates what default access rights will apply to IP packets that do not match any of the access restrictions.

mitelLogTableAllowSrcRouting.name: mitelLogTableAllowSrcRouting
mitelLogTableAllowSrcRouting.description: This indicates whether IP datagrams received on this interface and containing a source route option are to be discarded or accepted.

mitelFltGrpAccessRestrictTable.name: mitelFltGrpAccessRestrictTable
mitelFltGrpAccessRestrictTable.description: The IP Access REstriction configuration table.

mitelFltGrpAccessRestrictEntry.name: mitelFltGrpAccessRestrictEntry
mitelFltGrpAccessRestrictEntry.description: Contains information about a single IP Access filter.

mitelAccResTableIfIndex.name: mitelAccResTableIfIndex
mitelAccResTableIfIndex.description: Identifies the destination interface to which this filter apply.

mitelAccResTableOrder.name: mitelAccResTableOrder
mitelAccResTableOrder.description: Specifies the order that the filters on a destination are searched.

mitelAccResTableType.name: mitelAccResTableType
mitelAccResTableType.description: This object indicates what action should be taken when a match on this entry has occurred.

mitelAccResTableSrcAddrFrom.name: mitelAccResTableSrcAddrFrom
mitelAccResTableSrcAddrFrom.description: Defines the lower bound of the source IP address range. When determining address ranges, these four values are sequential: 255.255.255.254, 255.255.255.255, 0.0.0.0, and 0.0.0.1.

mitelAccResTableSrcAddrTo.name: mitelAccResTableSrcAddrTo
mitelAccResTableSrcAddrTo.description: Defines the upper bound of the source IP address range. When determining address ranges, these four values are sequential: 255.255.255.254, 255.255.255.255, 0.0.0.0, and 0.0.0.1.

mitelAccResTableSrcAddrOutsideRange.name: mitelAccResTableSrcAddrOutsideRange
mitelAccResTableSrcAddrOutsideRange.description: This indicates whether action is taken on values outside of the source IP address range or within that range.

mitelAccResTableDstAddrFrom.name: mitelAccResTableDstAddrFrom
mitelAccResTableDstAddrFrom.description: Defines the lower bound of the destination IP address range. When determining address ranges, these four values are sequential: 255.255.255.254, 255.255.255.255, 0.0.0.0, and 0.0.0.1.

mitelAccResTableDstAddrTo.name: mitelAccResTableDstAddrTo
mitelAccResTableDstAddrTo.description: Defines the upper bound of the destination IP address range. When determining address ranges, these four values are sequential: 255.255.255.254, 255.255.255.255, 0.0.0.0, and 0.0.0.1.

mitelAccResTableDstAddrOutsideRange.name: mitelAccResTableDstAddrOutsideRange
mitelAccResTableDstAddrOutsideRange.description: This indicates whether action is taken on values outside of the destination IP address range or within that range.

mitelAccResTableProtocolFrom.name: mitelAccResTableProtocolFrom
mitelAccResTableProtocolFrom.description: Defines the lower bound of the protocol ID range. When determining protocol ID ranges, these four values are sequential: 254, 255, 0, and 1.

mitelAccResTableProtocolTo.name: mitelAccResTableProtocolTo
mitelAccResTableProtocolTo.description: Defines the upper bound of the protocol ID range. When determining protocol ID ranges, these four values are sequential: 254, 255, 0, and 1.

mitelAccResTableProtocolOutsideRange.name: mitelAccResTableProtocolOutsideRange
mitelAccResTableProtocolOutsideRange.description: This indicates whether action is taken on values outside of the protocol ID range or within that range.

mitelAccResTableSrcPortFrom.name: mitelAccResTableSrcPortFrom
mitelAccResTableSrcPortFrom.description: Defines the lower bound of the source port number range. When determining port number ranges, these four values are sequential: 65534, 65535, 0, and 1.

mitelAccResTableSrcPortTo.name: mitelAccResTableSrcPortTo
mitelAccResTableSrcPortTo.description: Defines the upper bound of the source port number range. When determining port number ranges, these four values are sequential: 65534, 65535, 0, and 1.

mitelAccResTableSrcPortOutsideRange.name: mitelAccResTableSrcPortOutsideRange
mitelAccResTableSrcPortOutsideRange.description: This indicates whether action is taken on values outside of the source port number range or within that range.

mitelAccResTableDstPortFrom.name: mitelAccResTableDstPortFrom
mitelAccResTableDstPortFrom.description: Defines the lower bound of the destination port number range. When determining port number ranges, these four values are sequential: 65534, 65535, 0, and 1.

mitelAccResTableDstPortTo.name: mitelAccResTableDstPortTo
mitelAccResTableDstPortTo.description: Defines the upper bound of the destination port number range. When determining port number ranges, these four values are sequential: 65534, 65535, 0, and 1.

mitelAccResTableDstPortOutsideRange.name: mitelAccResTableDstPortOutsideRange
mitelAccResTableDstPortOutsideRange.description: This indicates whether action is taken on values outside of the destination port number range or within that range.

mitelAccResTableTcpSyn.name: mitelAccResTableTcpSyn
mitelAccResTableTcpSyn.description: TCP header, synchronize sequence numbers flag.

mitelAccResTableMatchIn.name: mitelAccResTableMatchIn
mitelAccResTableMatchIn.description: Indicates whether the filter applies to datagrams received on the interface. Normally, either mitelAccResTableMatchIn or mitelAccResTableMatchOut should be enabled.

mitelAccResTableMatchOut.name: mitelAccResTableMatchOut
mitelAccResTableMatchOut.description: Indicates whether the filter applies to datagrams transmitted on the interface. Normally, either mitelAccResTableMatchIn or mitelAccResTableMatchOut should be enabled.

mitelAccResTableLog.name: mitelAccResTableLog
mitelAccResTableLog.description: Controls whether a log message is to be produced each time a datagram matches the filter.

mitelAccResTableTrap.name: mitelAccResTableTrap
mitelAccResTableTrap.description: Controls the generation of SNMP trap.

mitelAccResTableStatus.name: mitelAccResTableStatus
mitelAccResTableStatus.reference: Textual Conventions for Version 2 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (RFC 1443).
mitelAccResTableStatus.description: The current status of this entry.

mitelAccResTableCount.name: mitelAccResTableCount
mitelAccResTableCount.description: Records the number of datagrams that matched this instance.

mitelAccResTableTrapped.name: mitelAccResTableTrapped
mitelAccResTableTrapped.description: The mitelAccResTableTrapped trap indicates that a datagram has matched a mitelFltGrpAccessRestrictEntry that has the mitelAccResTableTrap enabled.
